+++Mantle Cyndro Cledar+++

Mantle smiled and then tapped a few buttons, and Cyndro lowered down, his 
face looking at the two robots from another panel. "Can I start, Mantle?" He 
inquired in a curious voice. Cyndro was very excited about getting new stuff 
to be able to keep in good condition and all those nice things.

"You sure can, Cyndro." Replied Mantle and then looked over at the scanners 
when they reported a large wave of nanobots moving out toward the 
Cybertronian Fire. They moved under the ground through the holes inbetween 
the earth, and soon reached the ship and began to take apart the underside 
at the exact center. Each nanobot took off a particle and brought it back to 
the Element.

Outside the battle was still raging and a bunch of shots hit the Element's 
shields, but the Element was too strong to be hurt by that. The shields were 
still at nearly 100%, and would stay there for quite a while unless these 
guys put more effort into their attacks, but Predacons were whimpy anyways. 
Cyndro aimed the Element's weapons and launched alot of lasers at 
Triggerhappy and the other robots that were firing at the Element.



Cledar jumped out of the way of the giant foot that tried to squish him and 
then fired his fusion cannon at it's owner. He was aiming for his chest.
